This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on December 23, 2016. The memorandum is titled "Providing an Order of Succession within the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service." The purpose of the memorandum is to establish the order of succession for the Director of the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service in the event that the Director is unable to perform their duties. According to the memorandum, the Deputy Director of Mediation Services and Field Operations will be the first in line to act as the Director, followed by the Deputy Director, and then the most senior Regional Director. The memorandum also includes exceptions and provisions, including the President's discretion to deviate from the order of succession if necessary. The memorandum concludes by stating that it does not create any legally enforceable rights or benefits.